Welcome to the W3C Media Working Group!

You can find more information about our group, including charter, participants list, and publications, here:

https://www.w3.org/groups/wg/media

The Working Group co-chairs are Jer Noble (Apple) and Chris Needham (BBC). Francois Daoust is our W3C team contact.

The Working Group does most of its work on Github, with each of our specifications developed in its own repository:

https://www.w3.org/PM/Groups/repositories.html?gid={{ group.id }}

We have a monthly teleconference, on the second Tuesday of each month.

- January, March, May, July, September, November: 14:00 US Pacific time
- February, April, June, August, October, December: 07:00 US Pacific time

You can find the connection details here:

https://lists.w3.org/Archives/Member/w3c-archive/2020Jan/0323.html

During meetings, the Working Group uses IRC to scribe and manage the speaker queue:

https://irc.w3.org/?channels=#mediawg

All participants are required to follow the W3C Code of Ethics and Professional Conduct:

https://www.w3.org/Consortium/cepc/

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us.

We look forward to your participation.

Kind regards,

The Media Working Group co-chairs:

Jer Noble (jer.noble@apple.com)
Chris Needham (chris.needham@bbc.co.uk)
